It's a system where you flip a switch to turn on a solenoid that kicks in when you're off the pedal so that the exhaust valve opens just near the top of the compression stroke. If the valve doesn't open then the air acts like a spring and the energy used to compress the air winds up forcing the piston back down again.

But if the valve opens just before the piston starts going back down, then the energy used to compress the air is lost. That's why you hear trucks going
>BRABRABRABRABRABRABRAPP
so that they can slow down using the engine rather than burning up their brakes.
